<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Tybrus on 08-14-2001 02:24 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I had to kick in my two cents worth here.  I've been frequenting the the EQAtlas site for roughly two months, and reading the message boards just as long.

I may have misread the posting, but did it not say that Verant has used your maps in a Strategy Guide, but that they don't want you publishing a book?

Anyhoo.  As for the book publishing, it is something I would encourage you to pursue with Verant.  My guess is that most people pull a map of Utah when they decide to drive cross-state.  Hrmmm... what about the people who take a week long trip, and pull out a brochure or book, looking for the fun and interesting places to visit... good thing the government doesn't consider them spoilers  :)  

It would certainly be nice if Verant would reconsider the publishing of a book... I'd buy it.  Geeze... I bought Velious and I can't even use that yet.   :)

... I'm having a hard time not turning into this into a rant, time to end it...

I like the shareware idea.  Add the Paypal icon, I'll download the PDF file and make my donation.

All the best to you Muse and good luck in your future... that goes for everyone out there.


Tybrus
Rogue of the 25th Sin

90% common sense, 10% genius.</TEXTAREA>
